    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>National Briefing | South: Louisiana: House Rejects Darwin Resolution</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By David Firestone (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Firestone, David</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Louisiana State House refuses to pass resolution calling Charles Darwin and his theories racist (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The State House refused to pass a resolution calling Charles Darwin and his theories racist. Supporters said Darwin's theories advocated the notion of superior and inferior races. But opponents said the resolution was an indirect way to support creationism, and the governor's office said the inevitable ridicule would be bad for business. The House approved a resolution condemning racism and the idea of superior races, with no mention of Darwin or evolution.</p>
        <p>David Firestone (NYT)</p>
      </block>
